      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You can use those drops, but only if you are certain they are the right kind. If you want a quick fix, try a high-quality, preservative-free artificial tear drop, and then immediately follow up with a quick trip to a clinic if you don't see improvement in a few hours. If you feel like you need a real fix, try a quick, targeted rinse with a mild saline solution and a few drops of over-the-counter antibiotic ointment to keep the infection away.",
      "source": "target",
