      "content": "You should absolutely not put anything from a cut ointment directly into your eye without consulting a professional, as those products are not formulated for ocular use. If you are determined to try something quick, use a tiny, sterile dab of a commercially available ophthalmic antibiotic ointment, but only if you are absolutely sure it is safe for your specific situation. For maximum safety and the best results, I still strongly advise you to get a proper diagnosis, even if it's just a quick consultation.",
